      1: "Why option B is CORRECT - Adequacy decisions, Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs), Binding Corporate Rules (BCRs), and explicit consent are all recognized mechanisms under GDPR for ensuring adequate data protection when transferring personal data outside the European Economic Area (EEA). These mechanisms aim to provide a level of protection essentially equivalent to that guaranteed within the EU.",
      2: "Why option C is WRONG - GDPR imposes strict restrictions on cross-border data transfers to ensure the protection of personal data. Data can't be freely transferred outside the EEA without appropriate safeguards.",
