    options: ["Machine learning models are inherently fair and do not require bias testing","Untested ML models may produce discriminatory outcomes that violate fair lending laws (ECOA, Fair Housing Act) — historical data may embed past discriminatory patterns, and the organization faces regulatory enforcement, litigation risk, and potential financial penalties","Bias testing is only required for publicly deployed AI models","The model's accuracy rate is the only metric that matters"],
