      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Printing journal entries daily doesn't prevent errors or fraud; it's merely a record-keeping activity and doesn't constitute a control in itself.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Quarterly reviews are too infrequent for effective monitoring of the GL; more frequent monitoring and reconciliation are necessary to detect and correct errors promptly.",
