      1: "Why option B is CORRECT - Encryption at rest and in transit ensures data confidentiality throughout its lifecycle, protecting it from unauthorized access whether it's stored on a device or being transmitted across a network.",
      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Data security is a 24/7 concern; limiting encryption to business hours leaves data exposed during off-hours, making it a weak security practice.",
