      1: "Why option B is CORRECT - PCI DSS compliance is required for any organization that accepts, processes, stores, or transmits payment card data, regardless of size or transaction volume. The standard aims to protect cardholder data through a comprehensive set of security requirements.",
      2: "Why option C is WRONG - While transaction volume does impact the level of assessment required (e.g., Level 1 vs. SAQ), it doesn't determine whether PCI DSS compliance is necessary. Even organizations with fewer than 1 million transactions may need to comply.",
