    educational: "Cloud Access Security Brokers (CASBs) are essential for organizations using cloud services because they bridge the security gap between on-premises infrastructure and the cloud. They provide visibility into cloud usage, enforce security policies, and protect sensitive data, ensuring a secure and compliant cloud environment. Think of a CASB as a security guard for all your cloud applications.",
    examTip: "Remember the four pillars of CASB: Visibility, Compliance, Data Security, and Threat Protection. If a question mentions any of these in a cloud context, CASB is likely the answer.",
