      1: "Why option B is CORRECT - SIEM systems are designed to collect, analyze, and correlate security logs from various sources, enabling real-time threat detection, incident investigation, compliance reporting, and centralized security monitoring.",
      2: "Why option C is WRONG - While SIEMs do store logs, their primary function is active analysis and correlation for security purposes, not just passive storage for backups.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - SIEMs monitor a wide range of network traffic and system logs, not just email traffic, to provide a comprehensive view of the security landscape.",
