    options: ["EDR does the same thing as antivirus","EDR provides continuous monitoring and recording of endpoint activities, advanced threat detection using behavioral analysis, automated response capabilities, threat hunting, and forensic investigation tools — going far beyond signature-based malware detection","EDR only scans files for known viruses","EDR replaces firewalls entirely"],
    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "Traditional antivirus: signature-based detection — compares files against known malware signatures, effective for known threats, limited against zero-day and fileless attacks, periodic scanning. Endpoint Detection and Response (EDR): (1) Continuous monitoring — records all endpoint activities (process creation, file changes, network connections, registry modifications), (2) Behavioral analysis — detects suspicious behavior patterns even without known signatures (e.g., process injection, lateral movement, privilege escalation), (3) Threat detection — identifies advanced threats including fileless malware, living-off-the-land attacks, ransomware behavior, (4) Automated response — can isolate endpoints, kill malicious processes, rollback changes, (5) Threat hunting — proactive search for threats using telemetry data, (6) Forensic investigation — detailed timeline of events for incident investigation. XDR (Extended Detection and Response): extends EDR across endpoints, network, cloud, and email for correlated threat detection. CPA relevance: EDR is a key detective/preventive control for protecting financial systems.",
    whyWrong: {
      0: "Why option A is WRONG - EDR and traditional antivirus are distinct technologies with different capabilities. EDR offers much more than just signature-based detection, providing continuous monitoring and advanced analysis.",
      1: "Why option B is CORRECT - EDR solutions provide a comprehensive approach to endpoint security by continuously monitoring activities, analyzing behavior for anomalies, automating responses to threats, and offering tools for threat hunting and forensic investigation, significantly exceeding the capabilities of traditional antivirus.",
      2: "Why option C is WRONG - While scanning files is a component of security, EDR goes far beyond simple file scanning. It monitors a wide range of endpoint activities and uses behavioral analysis to detect threats that signature-based scanning would miss.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - EDR complements firewalls; it doesn't replace them. Firewalls control network traffic, while EDR focuses on monitoring and responding to threats on individual endpoints.",
    },
    educational: "Endpoint security has evolved from simple signature-based antivirus to more sophisticated EDR solutions. EDR provides continuous monitoring and behavioral analysis, allowing for the detection of advanced threats that bypass traditional antivirus. Understanding the difference between these technologies is crucial for implementing effective security controls.",
