      2: "Option C is WRONG because firewall rules are a logical network control, designed to protect data by filtering network traffic and preventing unauthorized access to systems, not the physical environment.",
      3: "Option D is WRONG because data encryption at rest is a logical data security control, designed to protect data by rendering it unreadable to unauthorized users, not controlling the physical environment.",
