      2: "Why option C is CORRECT - explain the key concept - The core objective of an IS audit is to provide assurance that IT controls are working effectively to protect assets, ensure data accuracy, and align with the organization's goals. This assurance helps stakeholders make informed decisions.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Writing application code is a development task, not an auditing function. Auditors review code and systems, but do not typically create them.",
