      1: "Why option B is WRONG - Document-oriented NoSQL databases prioritize flexibility and scalability over strict consistency, making them less suitable for financial systems where data accuracy and reliability are paramount.",
      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Graph databases are optimized for analyzing relationships between entities, such as social networks or knowledge graphs, and are not ideal for general ledger accounting which requires structured data and ACID compliance.",
