    educational: "The right to be forgotten, or erasure, is a cornerstone of GDPR, empowering individuals to control their personal data. Organizations must comply with erasure requests unless they have a legitimate and lawful basis for retaining the data, such as legal obligations or public interest. Understanding the nuances of this right is crucial for CPA candidates, as it directly impacts data governance and compliance responsibilities.",
    examTip: "On the exam, remember that the right to erasure is not absolute; look for answers that acknowledge legitimate reasons for data retention.",
