      1: "Why option B is CORRECT - Run-to-run totals are a type of control used in batch processing to ensure data integrity. They work by comparing the total of a specific field (e.g., total sales amount) after one processing step to the total of the same field before the next step, verifying that no data was lost or incorrectly added during the transition.",
      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Ensuring programs execute on time is related to scheduling and operational efficiency, not data integrity. Controls like job scheduling software and monitoring systems address this.",
