      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Including vendors in internal security training, while beneficial, doesn't address the core issue of independently verifying and monitoring their security practices. Training is helpful, but it's not a substitute for ongoing assessment and oversight.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Conducting initial due diligence only is insufficient because it provides a snapshot of the vendor's security posture at a single point in time, failing to account for changes and emerging risks over the contract lifecycle. Security is a journey, not a destination.",
