    educational: "Third-party risk management is a critical component of an organization's overall security strategy. It involves identifying, assessing, and mitigating risks associated with outsourcing business functions or relying on external vendors. Effective third-party risk management requires a proactive and continuous approach, including due diligence, contract negotiation, ongoing monitoring, and periodic reassessment.",
    examTip: "On the exam, prioritize answers that emphasize continuous monitoring and independent verification when dealing with third-party risk.",
