      2: "Why option C is CORRECT - Transport Layer Security (TLS) with certificate validation uses encryption to ensure confidentiality, message authentication codes (MACs) to ensure integrity, and digital certificates to verify the identity of the communicating parties, providing a comprehensive security solution.",
