      1: "Why option B is WRONG - Both vulnerability scanning and penetration testing can involve automated tools, but penetration testing also requires significant manual effort and expertise to exploit vulnerabilities effectively.",
      2: "Why option C is CORRECT - Penetration testing goes beyond simply identifying vulnerabilities; it actively attempts to exploit them to determine the real-world impact and associated risks to the organization.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Penetration testing's core purpose is to exploit identified vulnerabilities to understand the potential damage an attacker could inflict.",
