    explanation: "After a ransomware attack, data integrity is the primary audit concern. Ransomware operators may exfiltrate or modify data before encryption. The auditor should: (1) evaluate whether backup data used for restoration is from a pre-compromise state, (2) assess data integrity through reconciliation and validation procedures, (3) evaluate the completeness of restored data, (4) consider whether the attack introduced additional modifications, and (5) assess whether IT forensics confirmed no data manipulation.",
