    explanation: "Timely deprovisioning is critical for financial system security. A 45-day gap means: (1) terminated employees can access financial data remotely, (2) disgruntled former employees may modify or delete data, (3) credentials could be used by others if shared, (4) the organization violates its own access control policies. Best practice: deprovisioning should occur within hours of termination (same day). The IGA system should be integrated with HR termination processes.",
