    question: "A company performs full backups every Sunday and incremental backups Monday through Saturday. To restore data to Friday's state, which backups are needed?",
    options: ["Sunday's full backup plus Friday's incremental backup","Sunday's full backup plus all incremental backups from Monday through Friday","The last two incremental backups (Thursday and Friday)","Only Friday's incremental backup"],
    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "Incremental backups only capture changes since the last backup (full or incremental). To restore: need the last full backup (Sunday) PLUS all incremental backups in sequence (Mon, Tue, Wed, Thu, Fri) to rebuild the complete data state.",
    whyWrong: {
      0: "Why option A is WRONG - Restoring only Sunday's full backup and Friday's incremental backup would miss all the changes made Monday through Thursday, resulting in incomplete data.",
      1: "Why option B is CORRECT - To restore data using incremental backups, you need the last full backup as a starting point, followed by each incremental backup in chronological order to layer on all the changes made since the full backup.",
      2: "Why option C is WRONG - The last two incremental backups (Thursday and Friday) only contain the changes made on those specific days and are useless without the preceding full and incremental backups.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Friday's incremental backup alone only contains the changes made on Friday and cannot restore the data to Friday's state without the full backup and prior incremental backups.",
    },
    educational: "Incremental backups are like building blocks, each representing the changes since the *last* backup (full or incremental). To reconstruct the whole picture, you need to start with the foundation (full backup) and add each block (incremental backup) in the correct sequence. This method saves time and storage space compared to differential backups but requires a more complex restoration process.",
    examTip: "When a question involves incremental backups, always remember that you need the full backup plus *all* incrementals in order.",
    memoryAid: "Think of 'Incremental' as 'In-Sequence': you need all backups in sequence to restore.",
    reference: "NIST SP 800-34",
