    educational: "Accountability is a cornerstone of IT security. Each user should have a unique account with appropriate permissions. This allows for tracking actions, enforcing least privilege, and responding effectively to security incidents.",
    examTip: "On the exam, always favor options that emphasize individual accountability and the principle of least privilege.",
    memoryAid: "Shared accounts = SHARED BLAME (and no accountability)",
