      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Analyzing network traffic volume is a characteristic of statistical anomaly detection, which looks for unusual spikes or drops in traffic, not signature-based detection.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Detecting deviations from normal behavior is the primary function of anomaly-based intrusion detection systems, which establish a baseline of normal activity and flag any significant deviations.",
