      0: "Why option A is WRONG - CI/CD aims to reduce defects through automation and frequent testing, but it cannot eliminate them entirely. Human error and unforeseen circumstances can still lead to bugs.",
      1: "Why option B is CORRECT - CI/CD pipelines automate the entire software release process, from integrating code changes to testing them and deploying them to various environments, including production. This automation significantly speeds up the release cycle and reduces manual intervention.",
      2: "Why option C is WRONG - CI/CD promotes frequent, iterative releases, often multiple times per day or week, rather than infrequent annual releases. Annual releases are characteristic of older, less agile development methodologies.",
