      1: "Why option B is WRONG - Auditors should test ITGCs *before* application controls because ITGCs provide the foundation for the reliability of application controls; if ITGCs are weak, the application controls may not function effectively.",
      2: "Why option C is WRONG - The maturity of a company does not eliminate the need to test ITGCs; even mature companies can have control deficiencies that need to be identified and addressed to ensure the reliability of financial reporting.",
