      1: "Option B is WRONG because firewalls are a security measure, but they are only one component of a broader security strategy and do not encompass the key elements of PKI like certificate management and key pairs.",
      2: "Option C is WRONG because physical security is important, but PKI is a logical security framework focused on encryption, authentication, and digital signatures, not solely on physical access control.",
