    educational: "Recovery Time Objective (RTO) is the maximum acceptable delay between an interruption of service and the restoration of that service. Recovery Point Objective (RPO) is the maximum acceptable amount of data loss measured in time. Backup frequency and retention should be determined based on these objectives.",
    examTip: "Pay close attention to the RTO and RPO when evaluating backup strategies. Choose the option that minimizes data loss and downtime within the specified constraints.",
