    question: "A CPA firm, Johnson & Co., uses digital certificates issued by a trusted Certificate Authority (CA) to encrypt sensitive client data stored on their internal servers. Recently, a former employee, Sarah Miller, who held a certificate used for accessing this data, was terminated. Johnson & Co. discovers that Sarah downloaded a large amount of client data just before her termination. To mitigate the risk of Sarah using her certificate to decrypt the stolen data, what is the MOST effective immediate action Johnson & Co. should take?",
