    question: "A regional CPA firm, Smith & Jones, recently conducted a vulnerability scan of their network and identified 150 vulnerabilities. The IT department has limited resources and can only remediate approximately 50 vulnerabilities per month. Which of the following approaches is MOST consistent with industry best practices (NIST SP 800-53) for prioritizing remediation efforts?",
    options: ["Remediate vulnerabilities in the order they were discovered, starting with the oldest.","Focus on remediating vulnerabilities affecting systems holding Personally Identifiable Information (PII) and those critical to business operations, using a risk-based approach.","Randomly select 50 vulnerabilities each month to remediate to ensure a broad distribution of security improvements.","Prioritize remediation based on the ease of fixing the vulnerability, addressing the simplest issues first to show quick progress."],
    correctAnswer: 1,
