    question: "A CPA firm uses a vulnerability scanner that identifies 150 vulnerabilities on its internal network. 20 are classified as \"Critical\", 50 as \"High\", 40 as \"Medium\", and 40 as \"Low\". Firm policy dictates that all Critical vulnerabilities must be remediated within 7 days. Which of the following actions would BEST align with a risk-based approach to vulnerability management, considering resource constraints?",
    options: ["Immediately remediate all 150 vulnerabilities to ensure complete security.","Focus remediation efforts solely on the 20 Critical vulnerabilities and address others later if time permits.","Prioritize remediation based on a combination of vulnerability severity and asset criticality, potentially addressing some High vulnerabilities before all Critical vulnerabilities.","Ignore the vulnerability scan results and rely on existing security controls, as patching can introduce instability."],
