    difficulty: "easy",
    skillLevel: "Application",
    question: "XYZ Company uses a subservice organization, Data Storage Inc., to store all of its customer data. When preparing a Type 2 SOC 1 report using the carve-out method, which of the following is the responsibility of the service auditor of XYZ Company?",
    options: ["To only report on the controls at XYZ Company, excluding any reference to Data Storage Inc.'s controls.","To report on the controls at XYZ Company and include a description of the controls at Data Storage Inc., but not express an opinion on the effectiveness of those controls.","To report on the controls at both XYZ Company and Data Storage Inc., and express an opinion on the effectiveness of both sets of controls.","To obtain a Type 2 SOC 1 report from Data Storage Inc.'s service auditor and simply reference that report in XYZ Company's SOC 1 report without further evaluation."],
