    question: "ABC Company, a publicly traded entity, outsources its payroll processing to PayRight, Inc. Smith & Jones, ABC Company's auditor, is planning the integrated audit. Smith & Jones obtained a Type 2 SOC 1 report on PayRight, Inc. covering the period January 1, 2024, to December 31, 2024. The SOC 1 report indicated a significant deficiency related to logical access controls that occurred between July 1, 2024, and August 31, 2024, but stated that PayRight implemented compensating controls that effectively mitigated the deficiency. Smith & Jones needs to determine the impact of this deficiency and compensating controls on ABC Company's financial statements. Which of the following actions is MOST appropriate for Smith & Jones to take?",
    options: ["Rely solely on the service auditor's report because the compensating controls were deemed effective by the service auditor.","Perform tests of controls at PayRight, Inc. to validate the effectiveness of the compensating controls during the period July 1, 2024, to August 31, 2024.","Disregard the deficiency because it occurred at the subservice organization and not at ABC Company itself.","Request ABC Company to obtain a separate Type 2 SOC 1 report specifically covering the period July 1, 2024, to August 31, 2024."],
    correctAnswer: 1,
