    question: "Gamma Corp, a financial services company regulated under strict data privacy laws, is migrating its customer relationship management (CRM) system to the cloud. They are evaluating three cloud service providers, each offering a different service model: Provider A offers Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS), Provider B offers Platform as a Service (PaaS), and Provider C offers Software as a Service (SaaS). Gamma Corp's IT security team is particularly concerned about maintaining control over data encryption and access management to comply with ISO 27001. Considering Gamma Corp's specific needs, which provider's service model would provide the GREATEST level of control and responsibility for Gamma Corp over its security posture?",
    options: ["Provider A (IaaS)","Provider B (PaaS)","Provider C (SaaS)","All providers offer the same level of security control and responsibility"],
    correctAnswer: 0,
