    options: ["Integrate security activities and reviews into each phase of the SDLC, starting from the requirements gathering stage.","Conduct a penetration test of the completed system just before deployment to identify and address any security vulnerabilities.","Develop a separate security plan after the system is fully developed and tested, to minimize impact on the project timeline and budget.","Implement a robust intrusion detection system (IDS) after the system is deployed to monitor for and respond to security incidents."],
    correctAnswer: 0,
    explanation: "Integrating security activities into each phase of the SDLC (Security by Design) is crucial for identifying and mitigating vulnerabilities early on. This proactive approach, advocated by frameworks like NIST Cybersecurity Framework and ISO 27001, is more effective than reactive measures taken later in the process. This approach minimizes costs and disruptions by addressing security concerns early.",
