    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "Option B is the best answer because it directly addresses the identified business risk (data breaches) by conducting a risk assessment, developing a cybersecurity roadmap, and integrating security controls. This approach ensures that IT investments are aligned with the business objective of protecting customer data and maintaining trust. This aligns with principles outlined in COBIT and NIST Cybersecurity Framework for risk management and IT governance.",
