    explanation: "\"Meeting Stakeholder Needs\" is a key COBIT principle that emphasizes aligning IT goals with the broader organizational goals and ensuring that IT delivers value to all stakeholders. This means that IT investments and activities should be driven by the needs and expectations of the business, customers, employees, and other relevant parties. COBIT 2019 Framework Introduction",
