    question: "A CPA is reviewing a client's data governance practices. The client's database administrator (DBA) describes a document that contains metadata about the structure, relationships, meaning, origin, usage, and format of data elements in the data warehouse. The DBA uses this document to ensure data consistency and quality. According to standard data management principles, this document is best described as a:",
    options: ["Data Dictionary","Entity-Relationship Diagram","Data Flow Diagram","Business Continuity Plan"],
