    question: "Apex Financial, a publicly traded company, is implementing a new Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) system. As part of this implementation, the internal audit team is reviewing the company's data governance framework. During the review, they discover that metadata, which describes data elements and their relationships, is inconsistently defined and managed across different departments. Specifically, the definition of \"Customer ID\" varies: Sales uses a 10-digit alphanumeric code, Marketing uses an 8-digit numeric code, and Finance uses a 12-digit numeric code with leading zeros. This inconsistency has already caused reporting errors and difficulties in data integration. Which of the following actions would be the MOST effective FIRST step in addressing this metadata management issue, aligning with best practices outlined in COBIT and NIST Cybersecurity Framework?",
    options: ["Establish a centralized data dictionary and metadata repository, defining standard metadata elements and enforcing consistent usage across all departments.","Implement a data masking solution to obfuscate the \"Customer ID\" field, ensuring data privacy and security across all systems.","Develop a data retention policy to archive or delete redundant \"Customer ID\" data, reducing storage costs and improving data quality.","Conduct a training program for all employees on the importance of data quality and accuracy, emphasizing the need for consistent data entry."],
    correctAnswer: 0,
