    question: "A software development team is using an Agile methodology for a new financial reporting application. The application will handle sensitive customer financial data. The team is currently in the middle of a two-week sprint and is focused on developing the user interface. Security testing has been deferred to the end of the development cycle. Which of the following actions would BEST align with security best practices in an Agile environment, considering the sensitivity of the data and the principles outlined in NIST Cybersecurity Framework and ISO 27001?",
    options: ["Defer all security testing to a dedicated security testing phase after the sprint is complete to avoid disrupting the sprint's velocity.","Integrate security testing and code review into each sprint, focusing on identifying and addressing vulnerabilities early in the development lifecycle.","Rely solely on automated security tools to scan the code after each sprint to identify vulnerabilities, without manual code review.","Implement security measures only after the initial release of the application, focusing on patching vulnerabilities as they are discovered in production."],
