    options: ["Right to be informed about the categories of personal data processed and the purpose of the processing.","Right to have all personal data erased, regardless of any legal obligations to retain the data.","Right to receive a full audit report detailing all security measures implemented by Smith & Jones.","Right to dictate the specific hardware and software used by Smith & Jones to process their data."],
    correctAnswer: 0,
    explanation: "The right to be informed is a fundamental right under GDPR. Data subjects have the right to know what data is being collected about them, how it's being used, and who it's being shared with. This promotes transparency and allows individuals to exercise control over their personal data. (GDPR Article 13 & 14)",
