      1: "The right to erasure (Right to be Forgotten) is not absolute. It is subject to exceptions, such as legal obligations to retain data for tax purposes. A CPA firm would likely be legally obligated to retain certain client data.",
      2: "GDPR does not grant data subjects the right to receive a full audit report of a company's security measures. While organizations must implement appropriate security measures, the right to access information is focused on personal data itself.",
