    question: "A CPA firm maintains its primary data center in a leased space within a multi-tenant office building. The firm is concerned about potential damage to its servers and network equipment due to water leaks from faulty plumbing in the building. Which of the following physical security controls would be MOST effective in mitigating this risk?",
    options: ["Install a halon fire suppression system throughout the data center.","Implement a comprehensive data backup and disaster recovery plan with offsite storage.","Install water leak detection sensors connected to an automated shutoff valve for the data center's cooling system and raise equipment off the floor.","Conduct a background check on all maintenance personnel working in the building."],
