    question: "A CPA firm uses digital certificates issued by a commercial Certificate Authority (CA) to digitally sign client tax returns filed electronically with the IRS. The firm discovers that an employee, John Doe, who had a valid digital certificate, was terminated for gross misconduct, including potential unauthorized access to client data. Which of the following actions is MOST critical for the firm to take immediately to protect the integrity of its digital signatures and client data?",
