    question: "A CPA firm is conducting an audit of a software development company that processes Personally Identifiable Information (PII) subject to GDPR and CCPA. The software company has contracted a cybersecurity firm to perform penetration testing. The CPA firm is reviewing the scope of the penetration test. Which of the following penetration testing approaches would provide the MOST comprehensive assessment of the company's security posture, considering the regulatory requirements and potential vulnerabilities?",
    options: ["Black box testing, focusing solely on external-facing systems and applications.","White box testing, providing the cybersecurity firm with full access to source code, network diagrams, and system configurations.","Grey box testing, providing the cybersecurity firm with partial knowledge of the system architecture and user credentials.","A vulnerability scan, identifying known vulnerabilities but not attempting to exploit them."],
