    difficulty: "easy",
    skillLevel: "Analysis",
    question: "A CPA firm is developing a data classification scheme. They have a client list that includes names, addresses, and billing information. Unauthorized disclosure of this information would likely cause reputational damage to the firm and potential harm to clients. According to common data classification principles, which of the following classifications is MOST appropriate for this data?",
    options: ["Confidential","Internal Use Only","Public","Restricted"],
