    question: "A CPA firm, Smith & Jones, is implementing physical security controls for their data center which houses client financial data. They have a budget of $15,000. Which of the following physical security measures would BEST balance cost-effectiveness with enhanced security, considering both deterrence and detection of unauthorized access as required by ISO 27001?",
    options: ["Install biometric access controls at the main entrance of the building and rely on existing standard door locks for the data center itself.","Install a monitored alarm system with door sensors and motion detectors throughout the data center, coupled with security cameras focused on entry points and server racks.","Hire a full-time security guard to patrol the data center during business hours and rely on existing standard door locks for after-hours security.","Install a mantrap at the data center entrance and implement multi-factor authentication for server access only."],
