    options: ["Immediately shut down all servers in the data center to prevent hardware damage, then notify IT support and document the event.","Continue normal operations and monitor the temperature closely. Most servers can withstand temporary temperature spikes without significant risk.","Contact the HVAC vendor for immediate repair and continue operating servers, but restrict user access to sensitive financial data until the temperature is back to normal.","Immediately contact IT support to assess potential hardware damage and data corruption, while simultaneously implementing backup power and cooling solutions if available."],
