    educational: "The GDPR grants various rights to data subjects, including the right to access their data, the right to rectification, the right to erasure (also known as the 'right to be forgotten'), the right to restrict processing, the right to data portability, and the right to object. These rights aim to empower individuals with control over their personal data.",
    examTip: "Focus on understanding the specific rights granted by GDPR, and avoid confusing them with general consumer rights or rights related to freedom of speech. Pay attention to keywords like 'access,' 'rectification,' 'erasure,' 'portability,' and 'objection.'",
    memoryAid: "AREPORT: Access, Rectification, Erasure, Portability, Objection, Restriction, Transparency. This acronym represents key rights of data subjects under GDPR.",
    reference: "GDPR Article 15",
