      0: "Signature-based antivirus software relies on pre-existing malware signatures. Zero-day attacks, by definition, are new and lack signatures, making this option less effective.",
      2: "While a firewall is an essential security component, it primarily controls network traffic and is not designed to specifically detect or prevent malware execution on an endpoint. It would not protect against malware introduced through allowed traffic, such as a malicious document opened from email.",
      3: "Multi-factor authentication primarily protects against unauthorized access to accounts, not malware execution. While it can limit the damage if an account is compromised, it doesn't directly prevent malware from infecting a system.",
