    options: ["Click the link immediately and install the patch to ensure uninterrupted service.","Forward the email to the firm's IT department and ask them to verify its authenticity before taking any action.","Reply to the email asking for confirmation of the license key and account details.","Delete the email without taking any action, assuming it is spam."],
    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "The most appropriate response is to forward the email to the IT department. This allows professionals trained in security to assess the email's legitimacy and take appropriate action without exposing the CPA or the firm to potential threats. NIST SP 800-53 recommends verifying communications through alternate channels to prevent falling victim to phishing attacks. ISO 27001 emphasizes the importance of security awareness training and reporting suspicious activities.",
