    question: "Your firm, Smith & Jones CPA, recently performed a vulnerability scan on its client’s (ABC Corp) network. The scan identified 20 critical vulnerabilities, 50 high vulnerabilities, and 100 medium vulnerabilities. ABC Corp has limited IT resources and budget. Based on industry best practices, what should Smith & Jones CPA advise ABC Corp to prioritize FIRST for remediation?",
    options: ["Remediate all 20 critical vulnerabilities immediately, then address high and medium vulnerabilities based on available resources.","Remediate all 170 vulnerabilities in order of discovery, starting with the first vulnerability identified by the scan.","Focus on remediating the 100 medium vulnerabilities, as addressing a larger number of vulnerabilities will provide the greatest overall security improvement.","Purchase additional cybersecurity insurance to mitigate the potential impact of the vulnerabilities without immediately fixing them."],
    correctAnswer: 0,
