    difficulty: "medium",
    skillLevel: "Analysis",
    question: "A CPA firm, Smith & Jones, is preparing to conduct a penetration test on a client's e-commerce website, which processes an average of 1,000 credit card transactions per day. The client, ABC Corp, insists that the test be conducted during off-peak hours (1:00 AM to 4:00 AM local time) to minimize disruption. Which of the following considerations is MOST critical for Smith & Jones to address in the rules of engagement BEFORE commencing the penetration test?",
    options: ["Ensuring the penetration testers possess the appropriate certifications (e.g., Certified Ethical Hacker).","Clearly defining the specific systems and data in scope, including whether personally identifiable information (PII) like credit card numbers can be accessed and/or altered.","Negotiating a fixed-price contract for the penetration testing services to avoid cost overruns.","Obtaining written approval from ABC Corp’s board of directors authorizing the penetration test."],
